page.title: 13AN INTERVIEW WITH A RESIDENT
page.content: Mrs. Jackson is the village primary school secretary.She has lived in the village all of her life. There have been many changes in the village since she was a little girl.The village has grown and there are new private houses as well as a council estate. The building of the new by_pass road in 1984 has meant the loss of trade in the local shops and garages. In fact Mrs. Jackson has seen many shops in the village shut down as she has grown up,people preferring to go to the larger shops and supermarkets in the nearby towns of Wisbech and King's Lynn. Mrs. Jackson spent her time as a young girl listening to the radio, playing sport connected with school, being involved with Sunday School activities and having typing lessons.
